  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIf the beacon node is not ready when the validator starts, the validator will exit with error, see below\r\n\r\nFor automated environments, this will require wrapping the validator in \"wait-for-it\" or similar. While depends_on can make sure the beacon node is up, nothing prevents a race condition where the beacon node is not yet accepting connections when the validator starts.\r\n\r\nUnsure whether considered a bug or an enhancement: Validator could be in a try loop for the beacon until it finds the beacon or someone kills it. This is the approach your beacon takes for eth1 sources if I am not mistaken, and the approach the Lighthouse validator takes for beacon sources.\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nUnknown\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\nMinimal would be validator started before beacon.\r\nLess minimal may be a docker-compose environment with beacon and validator, but it'll take you a minute to reproduce a race condition.\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n<pre><code>\r\nprysm-validator_1         | time=\"2020-09-24 16:04:11\" level=fatal msg=\"Could not determine if beacon chain started: could not setup beacon chain ChainStart streaming client: rpc error: code = Unavailable desc = connection error: desc = \"transport: Error while dialing dial tcp 192.168.224.2:4000: connect: connection refused\"\" prefix=validator\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\nUbuntu 20.04.01\r\ndocker/docker-compose\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n1.0.0-alpha26\r\n",
